// The Business Deal
// 
// Original contract: Busicom exclusive rights
// Problem: Busicom financial troubles
// Solution: Reduce chip price, Intel keeps rights
// 
// Result:
// - Busicom gets cheaper chips
// - Intel can sell to anyone
// - Microprocessor industry born
// 
// Cost: ~$60,000 in discounts
// Value: Trillions of dollars of industry created

// November 15, 1971 - Intel Advertisement
// 
// 'A New Era of Integrated Electronics'
// 
// Intel 4004:
// - 4-bit parallel CPU
// - 45 instructions
// - 740 kHz clock
// - BCD arithmetic
// - 'Computing power comparable to ENIAC'
// 
// Price: $200 (dev kit), $60 (CPU only)

// Minimal CPU Architecture
// 
// Fetch:  instruction = ROM[PC]
// Decode: opcode = instruction[7:4]
//         operand = instruction[3:0]
// Execute:
//   if opcode == ADD: ACC = ACC + REG[operand]
//   if opcode == JMP: PC = operand
//   if opcode == LOAD: ACC = REG[operand]
//   ...
// Repeat
